//help resources Enter altitude above the Earth surface in kilometers. Enter flight Mach number or velocity in m/s. This values use to calculate inlet flow full parameters. If this value equals zero only static parameters will be displayed. Max Mach number value equals 21 because for so high velocities you should use more complicated models. Air static pressure in Pa. Air density in kg/m^3. Air static temperature in K. Full pressure of inlet flow in Pa. Enter Mach number or flow velocity to calculate this parameter. Enter Mach number to calculate this value. Full temperature of inlet flow in K. Enter Mach number or flow velocity to calculate this parameter. Enter Mach number to calculate this value. Sonic speed of the air in m/s for given parameters. Velocity in m/s or Mach number value of inlet flow. Dynamic pressure of the inlet flow in Pa with given altitude and Mach number. Enter Mach number or flow velocity to calculate this value. Enter altitude range in kilometers for parameters changing. Press OK button to generate graph. If no altitude was given program will work with default altitude range up to 50 kilometers.
